Veeshan Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchronomis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chronomis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/02 3:47:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27539.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heal III focus</span><hr size=1> Note that if druids got Superior Healing at 44, we would get benefit from the level 2 healing effect all the way to level sixty.  The way it stands now, a druid can be expected to get no healing benefit from focuses from the moment he reaches 51 up until he becomes uber enough to get one of those high end items.<br>
<br>
What <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> should</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have been implemented is multiple levels of each focus on reasonably obtainable items for the appropriate level, then better versions of each level of focus on rare or high end items.  Under that scheme a 52 druid would have a realistic chance of being able to focus a heal (in other words, appropriate equipment selection would improve him beyond just expanding his mana pool), but the 60 druid in a high end guild would be able to do it better through the use of a rare item.<br>
<br>
